# Observability & reliability

## Instrumentation

- Follow OpenTelemetry (OTel) conventions and standards for traces, metrics, and logs.
- Name spans, metrics, and attributes per OTel semantic conventions rather than ad-hoc
  names — consistent names make telemetry queryable and portable across tools.
- Prefer richer signals first: **traces → logs/events → metrics**. Instrument
  application-level behavior with traces (and structured events) before reaching for
  metrics; metrics are the last resort, for aggregates traces/events can't cheaply answer.

## Monitoring & alerting

- Alert on **user-facing symptoms**, not internal causes — a page should mean a real
  user is (or imminently will be) affected.
- Reserve human-facing notifications/paging for symptom-based, user-impacting alerts;
  the gold standard is **SLO burn-rate alerting**. Don't page on cause-level, internal,
  or speculative signals.
